post_summaries.description: The image shows two white bowls filled with Tangyuan, a Chinese dessert made of glutinous rice balls in a sweet soup. A white spoon is lifting one of the rice balls out of one of the bowls, showcasing its texture and color. The bowls are placed on a wooden surface, adding a natural and warm feel to the image.

The image shows two jars of homemade vegan Nutella surrounded by hazelnuts. A wooden spoon is shown with the Nutella dripping off of it into one of the jars. The post advertises a healthy, sugar-free version of Nutella made with hazelnuts, cocoa, agave, and olive oil.
The image shows a close-up of a bowl of dairy-free chickpea and vegetable soup. The soup is garnished with parsley and served in a decorative bowl.

The image shows a close-up of several Asian Peanut Pumpkin Pies, a traditional dessert common in Asia. The pies are golden-yellow and topped with black sesame seeds. The post encourages viewers to check out the recipe on the creator's YouTube channel.

The image shows three bowls of colorful hummus (green, yellow, and pink/beetroot) arranged on a wooden surface, garnished with chickpeas, herbs, and oil. The post is by hs.veganway and promotes a recipe for "3 Magic Creamy Hummus."

The image shows a close-up of vegan cinnamon rolls (Kanelbullar) topped with what appears to be chopped nuts. The caption mentions the recipe is vegan, without butter and uses eggless dough, and directs viewers to a YouTube channel for the full recipe.
